    "MissionGiver": "Ling Family Hauling",
    "Title": "Alliance Aid: Medical Cargo Haul - Medium Scale",
    "Description": "Hello,\n\nWe need your help! Medical supplies are in high demand after the Molina mold outbreak exhausted stockpiles. Thankfully, there's a medium scale haul of the stuff at <EM4>~mission(Location|Address)</EM4> ready to be brought to <EM4>~mission(Destination|Address)</EM4>.\n\nThis run needs a hauler with a ship that can hold <EM4>~mission(MissionMaxSCUSize) cargo containers</EM4>. You'll also need a <EM4>handheld tractor beam</EM4> to deal with the crates.    \n\nPlease let me know if you can handle this for us.   \n\nSafe Hauling,  \nReyes Ling \nCargo Logistics Coordinator\nLing Family Hauling\n\nLing Family Hauling knows it\u2019s a dangerous and unpredictable universe and has established several protocols to protect both you and our client\u2019s cargo. To ensure you aren\u2019t punished for circumstances outside of your control, total payment will be prorated to the percentage of cargo successfully delivered. A delivery timer will be set for each haul. Any cargo that remains undelivered upon its expiration will be flagged as stolen and treated as such. All pick-ups and deliveries must be autoloaded or done at a freight elevator.",
    "DisplayDescription": "Hello,\n\nWe need your help! Medical supplies are in high demand after the Molina mold outbreak exhausted stockpiles. Thankfully, there's a medium scale haul of the stuff at <EM4>Teasa Spaceport</EM4> ready to be brought to <EM4>[Destination|Address]</EM4>.\n\nThis run needs a hauler with a ship that can hold <EM4>4 SCU cargo containers</EM4>. You'll also need a <EM4>handheld tractor beam</EM4> to deal with the crates.    \n\nPlease let me know if you can handle this for us.   \n\nSafe Hauling,  \nReyes Ling \nCargo Logistics Coordinator\nLing Family Hauling\n\nLing Family Hauling knows it\u2019s a dangerous and unpredictable universe and has established several protocols to protect both you and our client\u2019s cargo. To ensure you aren\u2019t punished for circumstances outside of your control, total payment will be prorated to the percentage of cargo successfully delivered. A delivery timer will be set for each haul. Any cargo that remains undelivered upon its expiration will be flagged as stolen and treated as such. All pick-ups and deliveries must be autoloaded or done at a freight elevator.",
